---
applyTo: "source/**/*.py,extensions/**/*.py,scripts/**/*.py"
---

When editing Isaac Lab code:

- Keep configuration and runtime-heavy implementation modules separate when the repository already follows that split.
- Avoid eager imports of simulator packages from pure config modules; preserve existing `TYPE_CHECKING`, lazy export, or string-reference patterns when present.
- Mirror the repository's existing task or environment package layout instead of introducing a new hierarchy.
- When changing tasks or environments, review observations, actions, rewards, terminations, resets, scene setup, and docs together.
